(INS 330), ch\\u1ea5t \\u0111i\\u1ec1u ch\\u1ec9nh acid (INS 260), ch\\u1ea5t b\\u1ea3o qu\\u1ea3n (kali sorbate INS 202).<\\/p>\",\"element_en\":\"<p>Apricots, salt, monosodium glutamate, perilla, sweeteners (INS 955), cabbage red (INS 163 (v)), ethanol, antioxidants (INS 330), acid regulators (INS 260), preservative (potassium sorbate INS 202).<\\/p>\",\"element_jp\":\"\",\"date\":\"2020-05-25 14:18:17\",\"active\":\"1\",\"expiry_date\":null,\"preservation_id\":\"1\",\"deleted\":\"0\",\"units\":null,\"image\":{\"id\":\"100\",\"name\":null,\"date\":null,\"src\":\"\\/upload\\/images\\/636767470321985657PK003.jpg\",\"user_id\":null,\"deleted\":\"0\",\"size\":null,\"file_type\":null,\"real_name\":null,\"type\":\"2\"},\"price_km\":null,\"qty\":\"2\",\"unit_id\":0,\"amount\":190080}'),(5,4,189,2,0,0,'{\"id\":\"189\",\"code\":\"MS021\",\"price\":\"66000\",\"DVT\":null,\"name_jp\":\"\\u7d0d\\u8c46 \\u6975\\u5c0f\\u7c92 \\u305f\\u308c\\u4ed8 (\\u30e4\\u30de\\u30c0\\u30d5\\u30fc\\u30ba) - 147g\\/3\\u500b\",\"description_vi\":\"\",\"description_en\":\"\",\"origin_id\":\"1\",\"volume\":null,\"image_id\":\"542\",\"order\":\"0\",\"name_vi\":\"\\u0110\\u1eadu t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng l\\u00ean men Natto (YAMADA) - 147g\\/3 h\\u1ed9p\",\"name_en\":\"Frozen fermented soybean Natto (YAMADA) - 147g\\/3 box\",\"description_jp\":\"\",\"guide_vi\":\"<p style=\\\"TEXT-ALIGN: justify\\\">C&aacute;ch th\\u1ee9c d&ugrave;ng Nattou ch\\u1ebf bi\\u1ebfn s\\u1eb5n:<br><br>1. \\u0110\\u1ed5 g&oacute;i natto v&agrave;o trong ch&eacute;n, c\\u1eafm \\u0111\\u0169a v&agrave;o gi\\u1eefa r\\u1ed3i qu\\u1ea5y m\\u1ea1nh li&ecirc;n t\\u1ee5c theo v&ograve;ng tr&ograve;n kho\\u1ea3ng 40 l\\u1ea7n.<br><br>2. Th&ecirc;m gia v\\u1ecb:<br>N\\u1ebfu c&oacute; h&agrave;nh c\\u1ee7 th&igrave; cho h&agrave;nh c\\u1ee7 c\\u1eaft m\\u1ecfng v&agrave;o nattou, ti\\u1ebfp t\\u1ee5c qu\\u1ea5y qu\\u1ea5y m\\u1ea1nh kho\\u1ea3ng 20 \\u0111\\u1ebfn 30 v&ograve;ng. Ti\\u1ebfp theo l&agrave; cho g&oacute;i s\\u1ed1t tare v&agrave;o, r\\u1ed3i l\\u1ea1i ti\\u1ebfp t\\u1ee5c qu\\u1ea5y nh\\u1eb9 cho gia v\\u1ecb th\\u1ea5m v&agrave;o nattou. Sau c&ugrave;ng l&agrave; cho g&oacute;i m&ugrave; t\\u1ea1t v&agrave;o, v&agrave; ti\\u1ebfp t\\u1ee5c qu\\u1ea5y nh\\u1eb9, \\u0111\\u1ec3 cho m&ugrave;i m&ugrave; t\\u1ea1t kh&ocirc;ng bay h\\u1ebft.<br><br>3. Sau khi tr\\u1ed9n \\u0111\\u1ec1u, th&igrave; cho nattou v&agrave;o b&aacute;t c\\u01a1m, khi \\u0103n th&igrave; g\\u1eafp chung nattou v&agrave; c\\u01a1m r\\u1ed3i \\u0103n.<\\/p><p style=\\\"TEXT-ALIGN: justify\\\"><img style=\\\"height: 186px; width: 850px;\\\" alt=\\\"\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/125.253.113.12\\/\\/upload\\/images\\/ban.png\\\" class=\\\"fr-dii fr-draggable\\\"><\\/p><p style=\\\"TEXT-ALIGN: justify\\\"><strong>Ngu\\u1ed3n: Tabetai<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"guide_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">How to use processed Nattou:<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">1. Pour the natto packet into the bowl, stick the chopsticks in the middle, then stir vigorously in a circular motion about 40 times.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">2. Seasoning:<br>If there is an onion, thinly slice the onion into the nattou, continue to stir vigorously for 20 to 30 rounds. Next, add the tare sauce, then gently stir the seasonings to infuse into the nattou. Finally, put the mustard packet in, and continue to stir gently, so that the mustard smell doesn&apos;t go away.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">3. After mixing well, add nattou into the rice bowl, when eating, put together nattou and rice and eat.<\\/p><p><img class=\\\"fr-dib fr-draggable\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.foodzone.vn\\/public\\/uploads\\/2020-05-22\\/1590113509.png\\\" style=\\\"width: 1044px; height: 222.585px;\\\"><strong>Source: Tabetai<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"guide_jp\":\"\",\"detail_vi\":\"<p style=\\\"TEXT-ALIGN: justify\\\">Nattou l&agrave; m&oacute;n \\u0103n truy\\u1ec1n th\\u1ed1ng, d&acirc;n d&atilde; c\\u1ee7a ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi Nh\\u1eadt c&oacute; gi&aacute; tr\\u1ecb dinh d\\u01b0\\u1ee1ng r\\u1ea5t cao, \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ebf bi\\u1ebfn b\\u1eb1ng c&aacute;ch l&ecirc;n men \\u0111\\u1eadu t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng \\u1edf \\u0111i\\u1ec1u ki\\u1ec7n th&iacute;ch h\\u1ee3p, gi&uacute;p chuy\\u1ec3n h&oacute;a c&aacute;c enzyme, b\\u1ed5 sung th&ecirc;m m\\u1ed9t s\\u1ed1 vi khu\\u1ea9n c&oacute; l\\u1ee3i \\u0111\\u1ed3ng th\\u1eddi v\\u1eabn gi\\u1eef \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c c&aacute;c gi&aacute; tr\\u1ecb dinh d\\u01b0\\u1ee1ng c&oacute; s\\u1eb5n trong \\u0111\\u1eadu t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng. Th\\u01b0\\u1edfng th\\u1ee9c nattou c&oacute; nhi\\u1ec1u c&aacute;ch kh&aacute;c nhau, \\u0111\\u01a1n gi\\u1ea3n nh\\u1ea5t l&agrave; d&ugrave;ng k&egrave;m v\\u1edbi c\\u01a1m tr\\u1eafng. Ch\\u1ec9 c\\u1ea7n m\\u1ed9t b&aacute;t c\\u01a1m tr\\u1eafng, nattou, m\\u1ed9t ch&eacute;n shoyu l&agrave; c&oacute; th\\u1ec3 c\\u1ea3m nh\\u1eadn h\\u1ebft v\\u1ecb ngon c\\u1ee7a nattou, khi tr\\u1ed9n nattou v&agrave;o shoyu th&igrave; v\\u1ecb c\\u1ee7a natto tr\\u1edf n&ecirc;n ng\\u1eady h\\u01a1n v&agrave; ngon h\\u01a1n. nattou c&oacute; th\\u1ec3 \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ebf bi\\u1ebfn v\\u1edbi nhi\\u1ec1u h&igrave;nh th\\u1ee9c nh\\u01b0: Nattou sushi, Nattou n\\u01b0\\u1edbng, cho v&agrave;o trong s&uacute;p miso, \\u0103n chung v\\u1edbi salad hay trong m&oacute;n b&aacute;nh x&egrave;o Okonomiyaki.<\\/p><p style=\\\"TEXT-ALIGN: justify\\\">&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"detail_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Nattou is a traditional, rustic Japanese food that has a very high nutritional value, processed by fermenting soybeans in appropriate conditions, helping to metabolize enzymes, adding some beneficial bacteria. while preserving the nutritional value available in soybeans. Enjoying nattou has many different ways, the simplest is to use with white rice. Just a bowl of white rice, nattou, a cup of shoyu can feel the taste of nattou, when mixing nattou into shoyu, the taste of natto becomes more and mo