\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/HhlrjVFRwj0\\\"><span class=\\\"fr-video fr-dvi fr-draggable\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/HhlrjVFRwj0\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen=\\\"\\\"><\\/iframe><\\/span><\\/a><\\/p><p><strong>Recipe for Misoshiru (Soup Miso)<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Raw materials for making miso soup:<\\/p><ul><li>Broth, miso<\\/li><li>1 pack of dashi<\\/li><li>Tofu tenderly chopped<\\/li><li>Wakame (seaweed)<\\/li><li>Onions and scallions.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Making:<\\/p><p>- Add the broth to the boiling pot, dashi in and stir.<\\/p><p>- Boil at medium high heat, after boiling, reduce the temperature and simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes.<\\/p><p>- Add 1 tbsp of miso, stir well.<\\/p><p>- Cut the tofu into small pieces, stir gently to prevent the tofu from breaking.<\\/p><p>- Soak dried wakame in water.<\\/p><p>- Cut wakame, green onion, onion into the soup.<\\/p><p>- Pour water from the pot into the soup.<\\/p><p><img class=\\\"fr-dib fr-draggable\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.foodzone.vn\\/public\\/uploads\\/2020-05-21\\/1590045994.jpg\\\" style=\\\"width: 431px; height: 287.333px;\\\"><\\/p><pre data-placeholder=\\\"B\\u1ea3n d\\u1ecbch\\\" dir=\\\"ltr\\\">\\r\\n<\\/pre><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"guide_jp\":\"\",\"detail_vi\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">\\u0110\\u1eadu t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng l&ecirc;n men (Miso) l&agrave; m\\u1ed9t trong nh\\u1eefng lo\\u1ea1i t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng quan tr\\u1ecdng nh\\u1ea5t c\\u1ee7a v&ugrave;ng \\u0110&ocirc;ng Nam &Aacute;. \\u1ede Nh\\u1eadt h\\u01a1n 90% d&acirc;n s\\u1ed1 b\\u1eaft \\u0111\\u1ea7u m\\u1ed9t ng&agrave;y m\\u1edbi b\\u1eb1ng m\\u1ed9t c\\u1ed1c s&uacute;p miso n&oacute;ng b\\u1ed5 d\\u01b0\\u1ee1ng, t\\u0103ng s\\u1ee9c kho\\u1ebb thay v&igrave; u\\u1ed1ng c&agrave; ph&ecirc;. C\\u1ee9 \\u0111\\u1ec1u \\u0111\\u1eb7n v&agrave;o c&aacute;c bu\\u1ed5i s&aacute;ng ta \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c \\u0103n miso th&igrave; sinh l\\u1ef1c s\\u1ebd d\\u1ed3i d&agrave;o v&igrave; ch\\u1ea5t ki\\u1ec1m c\\u1ee7a n&oacute; k&iacute;ch th&iacute;ch th\\u1ec3 x&aacute;c v&agrave; tinh th\\u1ea7n.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">R\\u1ea5t nhi\\u1ec1u nghi&ecirc;n c\\u1ee9u c\\u0169ng cho th\\u1ea5y r\\u1eb1ng miso:<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-T\\u0103ng c\\u01b0\\u1eddng h\\u1ec7 mi\\u1ec5n d\\u1ecbch<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-Ng\\u0103n ng\\u1eeba ph&oacute;ng x\\u1ea1<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-Gi\\u1ea3m nguy c\\u01a1 b\\u1ecb c&aacute;c lo\\u1ea1i nh\\u01b0 ung th\\u01b0 v&uacute;, ung th\\u01b0 tuy\\u1ebfn ti\\u1ec1n li\\u1ec7t, ung th\\u01b0 ph\\u1ed5i v&agrave; ung th\\u01b0 ru\\u1ed9t k\\u1ebft<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-Gi&uacute;p da m\\u1ec1m m\\u1ea1i v&agrave; tr\\u1ebb trung(do c&oacute; ch\\u1ee9a axit linoleic)<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-Ch\\u1eadm l&atilde;o h&oacute;a do ch\\u1ee9a nh\\u1eefng th&agrave;nh ph\\u1ea7n ch\\u1ed1ng oxy h&oacute;a.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-Gi&uacute;p gi\\u1ea3m nh\\u1eefng d\\u1ea5u hi\\u1ec7u m&atilde;n kinh (do th&agrave;nh ph\\u1ea7n isoflavones, m\\u1ed9t lo\\u1ea1i oestrogen th\\u1ef1c v\\u1eadt \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c bi\\u1ebft \\u0111\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u1ec3n nh\\u1eb1m gi\\u1ea3m ch\\u1ee9ng b\\u1ed1c h\\u1ecfa t\\u1eebng c\\u01a1n)<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">-H\\u1ed7 tr\\u1ee3 c&aacute;c ch\\u1ee9c n\\u0103ng c\\u01a1 th\\u1ec3; t\\u0103ng kh\\u1ea3 n\\u0103ng t&aacute;i t\\u1ea1o v&agrave; duy tr&igrave; m\\u1ea1ch m&aacute;u v&agrave; x\\u01b0\\u01a1ng.<\\/p><p><br><br><\\/p>\",\"detail_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Fermented soybean (Miso) is one of the most important soybean varieties in Southeast Asia. In Japan more than 90% of the population starts the day with a cup of hot, nutritious miso soup, which increases health instead of drinking coffee. Every morning we eat miso, the energy will be abundant because its alkaline stimulates body and spirit.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">A lot of research also shows that misoImprove immune system<\\/p><ul><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Radiation prevention<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Reduce the risk of breast cancer, prostate cancer, lung cancer and colon cancer<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Leaves skin soft and youthful (due to its linoleic acid content)<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Delayed aging due to its antioxidant content.<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Helps reduce menopausal signs (due to the composition of isoflavones, a plant estrogen known to reduce hot flashes)<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Support body functions; Increase the ability to regenerate and maintain blood vessels and bones.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"detail_jp\":\"\",\"element_vi\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">\\u0110\\u1eadu t\\u01b0\\u01a1ng (kh&ocirc;ng bi\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u1ed5i gen) (30.4%), g\\u1ea1o, mu\\u1ed1i, chi\\u1ebft xu\\u1ea5t c&aacute; ng\\u1eeb, b\\u1ed9t c&aacute; ng\\u1eeb, chi\\u1ebft xu\\u1ea5t t\\u1ea3o b\\u1eb9, ch\\u1ea5t \\u0111i\\u1ec1u v\\u1ecb amino acid (E620),c\\u1ed3n Ethyl, n\\u01b0\\u1edbc<\\/p>\",\"element_en\":\"<p>Soybean (non-GMO) (30.4%), rice, salt, tuna extract, tuna powder, kelp extract, amino acid flavor enhancer (E620), Ethyl alcohol, water<\\/p>\",\"element_jp\":\"\",\"date\":\"2020-05-21 14:27:04\",\"active\":\"1\",\"expiry_date\":null,\"preservation_id\":\"3\",\"deleted\":\"0\",\"units\":null,\"image\":{\"id\":\"94\",\"name\":null,\"date\":null,\"src\":\"\\/upload\\/images\\/637101175070884781MS003.jpg\",\"user_id\":null,\"deleted\":\"0\",\"size\":null,\"file_type\":null,\"real_name\":null,\"type\":